  37 class ScopedValue : public Value
  38 {
  39 public:
  40     ScopedValue(const Span& span_, ContainerSymbol* containerSymbol_);
  41     bool IsComplete() const override { return false; }
  42     bool IsScopedValue() const { return true; }
  43     const ContainerSymbol* GetContainerSymbol() const { return containerSymbol; }
  44     ContainerSymbol* GetContainerSymbol() { return containerSymbol; }
  45     Value* Clone() const override { Assert(false, "scoped value cannot be cloned"); return nullptr; }
  46     void Write(BinaryWriter& writer) override {}
  47     void Read(BinaryReader& reader) override {}
  48     Value* As(TypeSymbol* targetType, bool cast, const Span& span, bool dontThrow) const override { Assert(false, "scoped value cannot be converted"); return nullptr; }
  49     void* IrValue(Emitter& emitter) override { Assert(false, "scoped value does not have ir value"); return nullptr; }
  50     TypeSymbol* GetType(SymbolTable* symbolTable) override { return type; }
  51     void SetType(TypeSymbol* type_) { type = type_; }
  52     Value* GetSubject() override { return subject.get(); }
  53     void SetSubject(Value* subject_) { subject.reset(subject_); }
  54 private:
  55     ContainerSymbol* containerSymbol;
  56     TypeSymbol* type;
  57     std::unique_ptr<Value> subject;
  58 };

 168 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>ValuesToLiterals(std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<Value>>&values, SymbolTable*symbolTable, bool&error)
 169 {
 170     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments;
 171     for (std::std::unique_ptr<Value>&value : values)
 172     {
 173         ValueType valueType = value->GetValueType();
 174         TypeSymbol* type = value->GetType(symbolTable);
 175         BoundLiteral* literal = new BoundLiteral(symbolTable->GetModule(), std::move(value), type);
 176         arguments.push_back(std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(literal));
 177     }
 178     return arguments;
 179 }

 181 std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<Value>>ArgumentsToValues(conststd::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>&arguments, bool&error, boolskipFirst, BoundCompileUnit&boundCompileUnit);
 182 
 183 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<Value>>ArgumentsToValues(conststd::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>&arguments, bool&error, BoundCompileUnit&boundCompileUnit)
 184 {
 185     return ArgumentsToValues(arguments, error, false, boundCompileUnit);
 186 }
 187 
 188 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<Value>>ArgumentsToValues(conststd::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>&arguments, bool&error, boolskipFirst, BoundCompileUnit&boundCompileUnit)
 189 {
 190     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<Value>>values;
 191     bool first = true;
 192     for (const std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>&argument : arguments)
 193     {
 194         if (first)
 195         {
 196             first = false;
 197             if (skipFirst)
 198             {
 199                 continue;
 200             }
 201         }
 202         std::unique_ptr<Value> value = argument->ToValue(boundCompileUnit);
 203         if (value)
 204         {
 205             values.push_back(std::move(value));
 206         }
 207         else
 208         {
 209             error = true;
 210             return values;
 211         }
 212     }
 213     return values;
 214 }

 216 template< typename ValueT  typename Op>
 217 Value* BinaryEvaluate(Value* left, Value* right, Op op, const Span& span)
 218 {
 219     ValueT* leftCasted = static_cast<ValueT*>(left);
 220     ValueT* rightCasted = static_cast<ValueT*>(right);
 221     return new ValueT(span, op(leftCasted->GetValue(), rightCasted->GetValue()));
 222 }
 223 
 224 template< typename ValueT  typename Op>
 225 Value* BinaryPredEvaluate(Value* left, Value* right, Op op, const Span& span)
 226 {
 227     ValueT* leftCasted = static_cast<ValueT*>(left);
 228     ValueT* rightCasted = static_cast<ValueT*>(right);
 229     return new BoolValue(span, op(leftCasted->GetValue(), rightCasted->GetValue()));
 230 }

 232 template<typename ValueT  typename Op>
 233 Value* UnaryEvaluate(Value* subject, Op op, const Span& span)
 234 {
 235     ValueT* subjectCasted = static_cast<ValueT*>(subject);
 236     return new ValueT(span, op(subjectCasted->GetValue()));

 769 
 770 void Evaluator::EvaluateBinOp(BinaryNode& node, BinaryOperatorFun* fun, Operator op)
 771 {
 772     node.Left()->Accept(*this);
 773     if (error)
 774     {
 775         return;
 776     }
 777     if (!value)
 778     {
 779         if (dontThrow)
 780         {
 781             error = true;
 782             return;
 783         }
 784         else
 785         {
 786             ThrowCannotEvaluateStatically(module, span, node.GetSpan());
 787         }
 788     }
 789     std::unique_ptr<Value> left(value.release());
 790     node.Right()->Accept(*this);
 791     if (error)
 792     {
 793         return;
 794     }
 795     if (!value)
 796     {
 797         if (dontThrow)
 798         {
 799             error = true;
 800             return;
 801         }
 802         else
 803         {
 804             ThrowCannotEvaluateStatically(module, span, node.GetSpan());
 805         }
 806     }
 807     std::unique_ptr<Value> right(value.release());
 808     if ((op == Operator::add || op == Operator::sub) && (left->GetValueType() == ValueType::pointerValue || right->GetValueType() == ValueType::pointerValue))
 809     {
 810         EvaluateAdditivePointerOp(node.GetSpan(), op, left, right);
 811         return;
 812     }
 813     if (op == Operator::comparison && left->GetValueType() == ValueType::pointerValue && right->GetValueType() == ValueType::pointerValue)
 814     {
 815         PointerValue* leftPtr = static_cast<PointerValue*>(left.get());
 816         PointerValue* rightPtr = static_cast<PointerValue*>(right.get());
 817         if (leftPtr->GetValue() != nullptr && rightPtr->GetValue() != nullptr && leftPtr->PointeeType() != rightPtr->PointeeType())
 818         {
 819             if (dontThrow)
 820             {
 821                 error = true;
 822                 return;
 823             }
 824             else
 825             {
 826                 throw Exception(module, "incompatible pointer types for comparison", node.GetSpan());
 827             }
 828         }
 829     }
 830     ValueType leftType = left->GetValueType();
 831     ValueType rightType = right->GetValueType();
 832     ValueType commonType = CommonType(leftType, rightType);
 833     ValueType operationType = commonType;
 834     if (targetValueType > operationType)
 835     {
 836         operationType = targetValueType;
 837     }
 838     TypeSymbol* type = GetTypeFor(operationType, symbolTable);
 839     if (!type)
 840     {
 841         if (dontThrow)
 842         {
 843             error = true;
 844             return;
 845         }
 846         else
 847         {
 848             throw Exception(module, "conversion from " + ValueTypeStr(leftType) + " to " + ValueTypeStr(operationType) + " is not valid", span);
 849         }
 850     }
 851     std::unique_ptr<Value> leftConverted(left->As(type, cast, node.GetSpan(), dontThrow));
 852     std::unique_ptr<Value> rightConverted(right->As(type, cast, node.GetSpan(), dontThrow));
 853     if (dontThrow)
 854     {
 855         if (!leftConverted || !rightConverted)
 856         {
 857             error = true;
 858             return;
 859         }
 860     }
 861     BinaryOperatorFun operation = fun[uint8_t(operationType)];
 862     value.reset(operation(module, leftConverted.get(), rightConverted.get(), node.GetSpan(), dontThrow));
 863 }

 865 void Evaluator::EvaluateAdditivePointerOp(const Span& span, Operator op, const std::std::unique_ptr<Value>&left, conststd::std::unique_ptr<Value>&right)
 866 {

 868     {

 913                 {

1071 void Evaluator::Visit(FunctionNode& functionNode)
1072 {
1073     bool fileScopeAdded = false;
1074     Symbol* symbol = symbolTable->GetSymbol(&functionNode);
1075     if (symbol->IsFunctionSymbol())
1076     {
1077         FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol = static_cast<FunctionSymbol*>(symbol);
1078         int n = functionSymbol->UsingNodes().Count();
1079         if (n > 0)
1080         {
1081             FileScope* fileScope = new FileScope(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule());
1082             FileScope* prevFileScope = currentFileScope;
1083             currentFileScope = fileScope;
1084             boundCompileUnit.AddFileScope(fileScope);
1085             fileScopeAdded = true;
1086             for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1087             {
1088                 Node* usingNode = functionSymbol->UsingNodes()[i];
1089                 usingNode->Accept(*this);
1090             }
1091             currentFileScope = prevFileScope;
1092         }
1093     }
1094     bool prevReturned = returned;
1095     DeclarationBlock* prevDeclarationBlock = currentDeclarationBlock;
1096     DeclarationBlock declarationBlock(span, U"functionBlock");
1097     currentDeclarationBlock = &declarationBlock;
1098     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
1099     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
1100     declarationBlock.GetContainerScope()->SetParentScope(containerScope);
1101     containerScope = declarationBlock.GetContainerScope();
1102     int nt = functionNode.TemplateParameters().Count();
1103     if (nt != templateTypeArguments.size())
1104     {
1105         if (dontThrow)
1106         {
1107             containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1108             currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1109             returned = prevReturned;
1110             error = true;
1111             return;
1112         }
1113         else
1114         {
1115             throw Exception(module, "wrong number of function template type arguments", span);
1116         }
1117     }
1118     for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
1119     {
1120         TemplateParameterNode* templateParameterNode = functionNode.TemplateParameters()[i];
1121         TypeSymbol* templateTypeArgument = templateTypeArguments[i];
1122         BoundTemplateParameterSymbol* boundTemplateParameter = new BoundTemplateParameterSymbol(span, templateParameterNode->Id()->Str());
1123         boundTemplateParameter->SetType(templateTypeArgument);
1124         declarationBlock.AddMember(boundTemplateParameter);
1125     }
1126     int n = functionNode.Parameters().Count();
1127     if (n != argumentValues.size())
1128     {
1129         if (dontThrow)
1130         {
1131             containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1132             currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1133             returned = prevReturned;
1134             error = true;
1135             return;
1136         }
1137         else
1138         {
1139             throw Exception(module, "wrong number of function arguments", span);
1140         }
1141     }
1142     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1143     {
1144         std::unique_ptr<Value> argumentValue = std::move(argumentValues[i]);
1145         TypeSymbol* argumentType = argumentValue->GetType(symbolTable);
1146         ParameterNode* parameterNode = functionNode.Parameters()[i];
1147         VariableValueSymbol* variableValueSymbol = new VariableValueSymbol(parameterNode->GetSpan(), parameterNode->Id()->Str(), std::move(argumentValue));
1148         variableValueSymbol->SetType(argumentType);
1149         declarationBlock.AddMember(variableValueSymbol);
1150     }
1151     functionNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
1152     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1153     currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1154     returned = prevReturned;
1155     if (fileScopeAdded)
1156     {
1157         boundCompileUnit.RemoveLastFileScope();
1158     }
1159 }

1384             ctorNode->Accept(*this);

1388                 {
1389                     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1390                     currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1391                     returned = prevReturned;
1392                     currentClassType = prevClassType;
1393                     error = true;
1394                     return;
1395                 }
1396                 else
1397                 {
1398                     ThrowCannotEvaluateStatically(module, span, ctorNode->GetSpan());
1399                 }
1400             }
1401         }
1402         else
1403         {
1404             if (dontThrow)
1405             {
1406                 containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1407                 currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1408                 returned = prevReturned;
1409                 currentClassType = prevClassType;
1410                 error = true;
1411                 return;
1412             }
1413             else
1414             {
1415                 ThrowCannotEvaluateStatically(module, span, constructorNode.GetSpan());
1416             }
1417         }
1418         memberValues.push_back(std::move(value));
1419     }
1420     constructorNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
1421     value.reset(new StructuredValue(span, classType, std::move(memberValues)));
1422     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1423     currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1424     returned = prevReturned;
1425     currentClassType = prevClassType;

1432 void Evaluator::Visit(MemberFunctionNode& memberFunctionNode)
1433 {
1434     bool fileScopeAdded = false;
1435     Symbol* symbol = symbolTable->GetSymbol(&memberFunctionNode);
1436     if (symbol->IsFunctionSymbol())
1437     {
1438         FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol = static_cast<FunctionSymbol*>(symbol);
1439         int n = functionSymbol->UsingNodes().Count();
1440         if (n > 0)
1441         {
1442             FileScope* fileScope = new FileScope(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule());
1443             FileScope* prevFileScope = currentFileScope;
1444             currentFileScope = fileScope;
1445             boundCompileUnit.AddFileScope(fileScope);
1446             fileScopeAdded = true;
1447             for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1448             {
1449                 Node* usingNode = functionSymbol->UsingNodes()[i];
1450                 usingNode->Accept(*this);
1451             }
1452             currentFileScope = prevFileScope;
1453         }
1454     }
1455     bool prevReturned = returned;
1456     DeclarationBlock* prevDeclarationBlock = currentDeclarationBlock;
1457     DeclarationBlock declarationBlock(span, U"functionBlock");
1458     currentDeclarationBlock = &declarationBlock;
1459     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
1460     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
1461     declarationBlock.GetContainerScope()->SetParentScope(containerScope);
1462     containerScope = declarationBlock.GetContainerScope();
1463     int n = memberFunctionNode.Parameters().Count();
1464     if (n != argumentValues.size())
1465     {
1466         if (dontThrow)
1467         {
1468             containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1469             currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1470             returned = prevReturned;
1471             error = true;
1472             return;
1473         }
1474         else
1475         {
1476             throw Exception(module, "wrong number of function arguments", memberFunctionNode.GetSpan());
1477         }
1478     }
1479     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1480     {
1481         std::unique_ptr<Value> argumentValue = std::move(argumentValues[i]);
1482         TypeSymbol* argumentType = argumentValue->GetType(symbolTable);
1483         ParameterNode* parameterNode = memberFunctionNode.Parameters()[i];
1484         VariableValueSymbol* variableValueSymbol = new VariableValueSymbol(parameterNode->GetSpan(), parameterNode->Id()->Str(), std::move(argumentValue));
1485         variableValueSymbol->SetType(argumentType);
1486         declarationBlock.AddMember(variableValueSymbol);
1487     }
1488     if (currentClassType && structureReferenceValue)
1489     {
1490         StructuredValue* structuredValue = nullptr;
1491         if (structureReferenceValue->IsStructuredReferenceValue())
1492         {
1493             structuredValue = static_cast<StructuredReferenceValue*>(structureReferenceValue.get())->GetStructuredValue();
1494         }
1495         else
1496         {
1497             if (dontThrow)
1498             {
1499                 containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1500                 currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1501                 returned = prevReturned;
1502                 error = true;
1503                 return;
1504             }
1505             else
1506             {
1507                 throw Exception(module, "structured reference value expected", memberFunctionNode.GetSpan());
1508             }
1509         }
1510         int n = currentClassType->MemberVariables().size();
1511         if (n != structuredValue->Members().size())
1512         {
1513             if (dontThrow)
1514             {
1515                 containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1516                 currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1517                 returned = prevReturned;
1518                 error = true;
1519                 return;
1520             }
1521             else
1522             {
1523                 throw Exception(module, "wrong number of structured value members", memberFunctionNode.GetSpan());
1524             }
1525         }
1526         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1527         {
1528             MemberVariableSymbol* memberVariableSymbol = currentClassType->MemberVariables()[i];
1529             Value* memberValue = structuredValue->Members()[i].get();
1530             ConstantSymbol* constantSymbol = new ConstantSymbol(span, memberVariableSymbol->Name());
1531             constantSymbol->SetModule(module);
1532             constantSymbol->SetType(memberVariableSymbol->GetType());
1533             if (memberValue->GetValueType() == ValueType::arrayValue)
1534             {
1535                 constantSymbol->SetValue(new ArrayReferenceValue(static_cast<ArrayValue*>(memberValue)));
1536             }
1537             else if (memberValue->GetValueType() == ValueType::structuredValue)
1538             {
1539                 constantSymbol->SetValue(new StructuredReferenceValue(static_cast<StructuredValue*>(memberValue)));
1540             }
1541             else
1542             {
1543                 constantSymbol->SetValue(memberValue->Clone());
1544             }
1545             declarationBlock.AddMember(constantSymbol);
1546         }
1547     }
1548     memberFunctionNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
1549     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
1550     currentDeclarationBlock = prevDeclarationBlock;
1551     returned = prevReturned;
1552     if (fileScopeAdded)
1553     {
1554         boundCompileUnit.RemoveLastFileScope();
1555     }
1556 }

1996 void Evaluator::Visit(ConstructionStatementNode& constructionStatementNode)
1997 {

2003             return;

2005         else

2009     }
2010     TypeSymbol* type = ResolveType(constructionStatementNode.TypeExpr(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope);
2011     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<Value>>values;
2012     int n = constructionStatementNode.Arguments().Count();
2013     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)

2021             {
2022                 error = true;

2024             }

2026             {
2027                 ThrowCannotEvaluateStatically(module, span, constructionStatementNode.GetSpan());
2028             }
2029         }
2030         values.push_back(std::move(value));
2031     }
2032     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>arguments=ValuesToLiterals(values, symbolTable, error);
2033     if (error)
2034     {
2035         if (dontThrow)
2036         {
2037             return;
2038         }
2039         else
2040         {
2041             ThrowCannotEvaluateStatically(module, span, constructionStatementNode.GetSpan());

4052 std::std::unique_ptr<Value>Evaluate(Node*node, TypeSymbol*targetType, ContainerScope*containerScope, BoundCompileUnit&boundCompileUnit, bool dontThrow, BoundFunction* currentFunction, const Span& span)
4053 {
4054     ValueType targetValueType = targetType->GetValueType();
4055     Evaluator evaluator(boundCompileUnit, containerScope, targetType, targetValueType, false, dontThrow, currentFunction, span);
4056     node->Accept(evaluator);
4057     if (evaluator.Error())
4058     {
4059         return std::unique_ptr<Value>();
4060     }
4061     else
4062     {
4063         std::unique_ptr<Value> value = evaluator.GetValue();
4064         if (value && value->IsComplete())
4065         {
4066             if (!TypesEqual(targetType->PlainType(span), value->GetType(&boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable())))
4067             {
4068                 if (targetType->IsArrayType() && static_cast<ArrayTypeSymbol*>(targetType)->Size() == -1)
4069                 {
4070                     return std::move(value);
4071                 }
4072                 if (value->IsStringReferenceValue())
4073                 {
4074                     return std::move(value);
4075                 }
4076                 value.reset(value->As(targetType->PlainType(span), false, node->GetSpan(), dontThrow));
4077             }
4078             return std::move(value);
4079         }
4080         else
4081         {
4082             if (dontThrow)
4083             {
4084                 return std::unique_ptr<Value>();
4085             }
4086             else
4087             {
4088                 throw Exception(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), "value not complete", node->GetSpan());
4089             }
4090         }
4091     }
4092 }
